Boulder-Estes Century
description: Inaugural century ride from Boulder to Estes Park & back, ride to benefit Colorado Search & Rescue.  45 mile option available.
course:
Boulder, thru Lyons into South St Vrain Canyon.  From Estes, North St Vrain canyon back to Lyons, then thru Boulder.  Finish with 7 miles on the Boulder Creek Path.
99.2 miles & 7ooo\\\' elevation gain/loss.
directions: Start/finish at Stazio Ballpark, located at Valmont & Butte Mill Rd, Boulder.

title: 11th Annual Beaver Meadows Mtb Festival

address.street: Beaver Meadows Resort Ranch; 100 Marmot Drive, Unit 1

description: Since 1995, CSU Rams Cycling has hosted a weekend of fun, excitement, and mountain biking. Located at the Beaver Meadows Resort Ranch in Beautiful Red Feather Lakes, CO; the weekend will be packed with biking fun. Beginning with the short track races in the morning, a downhill event in the afternoon, and the cross country and kids races on Sunday morning; Beaver Meadows MTB Festival has something for every level of rider.
course:
SHORT TRACK: Rippin\\\' fast fairly flat oval course circling the campground area.
DOWNHILL: A full throttle ride the whole way  down! Plenty of excitment including 6 foot drops, trees, rocks, and even a road crossing. 
CROSS COUNTRY: Course will be the same as 2005 race with a different or no half lap. Race will start and finish at Beaver Meadows Base Area. A shin to knee deep water crossing about 1/3 of the way around. 10 mile loop begins with 1.5 fairly flat miles on fir road and singletrack. After a 2.5 mile climb on double and singletrack and several miles of rolling, technical terrain, there is a fast, long descent to the base area. The finish will be just passed the main base area where the start and morning registration are.
KIDS RACE: two races: 5 and under and 6-9 years on Sunday midmorning. Course will vary based on participants but will be a shorter lap at the homestead cabin. More family events will be announced as race draws near.
registration:
Pre-registration available through active.com (visit www.ramscycling.com/bmrace for more info) 
NORBA races: $30 for first race and $20 for the second, collegiate $20 per race or $50 for all three.
notes:
Short track starts at 9am with each race 20 minutes long.
Downhill course will be open for practice from 2-6 friday and saturday from 9:30-12:30. First racer goes off aqt 2pm, start list posted around noon.
Cross country race starts at 9am. Categories will be staged to go off every five minutes. Pro / A first and Beginner / c categories last. Course is ten miles long - laps for all categories will be posted day of.
directions: Take I-25 north to HWY 14 west exit into Fort Collins (Mulberry st.), turn north to HWY 287 (College Ave) and go north for 21 miles to Livermore, at The Forks Restaurant turn left to county rd 74E. Continue on County Rd 74E for 24.5 miles towards Red Feather Lakes. Continue past the Red Feather Lakes turnoff until you see the Pot Belly restaurant on the right hand side, 1000ft past the Pot Belly and make a right turn to County Rd 73C. Continue 4.3 miles northwest to the Beaver Meadows Resort entryway. You will see a log sign with green and yellow letters. Continue straight past the log sign and follow the entryway. Map at ramscycling.com/bmrace
